22/12/2003
KERBALA, Iraq -- The mayor of Kerbala, Akram Mahdi al-Yassri, praised the role of the Bulgarian contingent in maintaining peace and security in his town Sunday (21 December). 
He met with Bulgarian Deputy Defence Minister Ilko Dimitrov, who handed over a donation of medical goods including serums and vaccines worth over 40,000 euros. 
Also on hand was the chief of the Bulgarian Land Forces Staff, Lieutenant General Zlatan Stoikov, other Karbala authorities and local religious leaders. 
The sheikhs' association of Karbala asked to send a delegation for talks with Bulgarian Muslims. 
(Trud - 22/12/03; BTA, BNT - 21/12/03)
